HEADWORD: Carpellum
<hw>Car*pel"lum</hw> <pr>(-p⟦ecr⟧l"l⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>carpellum</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>karpo`s</grk>
fruit.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A simple pistil or single-celled
ovary or seed vessel, or one of the parts of a compound pistil, ovary,
or seed vessel. See <xex>Illust</xex> of <er>Carpaphore</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

